    S - a RadioSource type.
    public class MSACRobustRangingAndRssiRadioSourceEstimator2D<S extends RadioSource>
extends RobustRangingAndRssiRadioSourceEstimator2D<S>
    Robustly estimate 2D position, transmitted power and pathloss exponent of a radio source (e.g. WiFi access point or bluetooth beacon), by discarding outliers using MSAC algorithm and assuming that the ranging data is available to obtain position with greater accuracy and that the radio source emits isotropically following the expression below: Pr = Pt*Gt*Gr*lambda^2 / (4*pi*d)^2, where Pr is the received power (expressed in mW), Gt is the Gain of the transmission antenna Gr is the Gain of the receiver antenna d is the distance between emitter and receiver and lambda is the wavelength and is equal to: lambda = c / f, where c is the speed of light and f is the carrier frequency of the radio signal. Because usually information about the antenna of the radio source cannot be retrieved (because many measurements are made on unknown devices where physical access is not possible), this implementation will estimate the equivalent transmitted power as: Pte = Pt * Gt * Gr. If Readings contain RSSI standard deviations, those values will be used, otherwise it will be assumed an RSSI standard deviation of 1 dB.
